Package com.credenceid.database

Enum BiometricDatabase.Status

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<BiometricDatabase.Status>
      • com.credenceid.database.BiometricDatabase.Status
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<BiometricDatabase.Status>
    Enclosing interface:
    BiometricDatabase
    public static enum BiometricDatabase.Status
extends java.lang.Enum<BiometricDatabase.Status>
    Possible operation status codes returned inside callback(s) of following API(s).

    • BiometricDatabase.enroll(int, FingerprintRecord, FaceRecord, IrisRecord, OnEnrollCallback)
    • BiometricDatabase.enroll(int, FingerprintRecord[], FaceRecord, IrisRecord[], OnEnrollCallback)
    • BiometricDatabase.read(int, OnReadCallback)
    • BiometricDatabase.verify(int, FingerprintRecord[], FaceRecord, IrisRecord[], OnVerifyCallback)
    • BiometricDatabase.verify(int, FingerprintRecord[], FaceRecord, IrisRecord[], OnVerifyCallback)
    • BiometricDatabase.match(FingerprintRecord, FaceRecord, IrisRecord, OnMatchCallback)
    • BiometricDatabase.match(FingerprintRecord[], FaceRecord, IrisRecord[], OnMatchCallback)
    • BiometricDatabase.delete(int, OnDeleteCallback)

    • Enum Constant Summary

      Enum Constants 
      Enum Constant Description
      ERR_BAD_FACE_DATA
      Indicates that given face data is invalid.
      ERR_BAD_FINGERPRINT_DATA
      Indicates that given fingerprint data is invalid.
      ERR_BAD_IRIS_DATA
      Indicates that given iris data is invalid.
      ERR_DB_READ_WRITE
      This code is returned if there was an error reading/writing to database.
      ERR_NO_DATA
      Used by BiometricsDatabase.enroll() APIs to indicate that no data was given to actually enroll.
      ERR_RECORD_ALREADY_EXISTS
      Indicates that a record for a given ID already exists in database.
      ERR_RECORD_NOT_FOUND
      Indicates that record with given ID was not found in database.
      INACTIVE_API
      Used by all database APIs to indicate that API ID is not in active list.
      LICENSE_ERROR
      This codee is returned if there is no license available for databsse APIs.
      NO_MATCH
      Used by BiometricsDatabase.match() and BiometricsDatabase.verify ()APIs to indicate that at-least one match occurred.
      SUCCESS
      Indicates operation successfully completed.
      UNKNOWN
      This is only used as a place holder for Bundles to un-parse out Status int code.
